    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen setting the local `winhighlight` for `WinSeparator`, only the right border of the window will be affected.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:e /tmp/foo\r\n<C-w>v\r\n:e /tmp/bar\r\n:setlocal winhighlight=WinSeparator:Error\r\n<C-w>L\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe window separator for `/tmp/bar` should stay red, even after you move the window to the right with `<C-w>L`.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.0-dev-606+g628f6cce8\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nvim does not have the `winhighlight` option\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.28.1\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbob",
