            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Because split separators are a single column, they can't be divided between adjacent windows. This is just a vim (TUI) limitation.\r\n\r\nYeah, I've realized this, which is why I mentioned the potential conflict handling.\r\n\r\nCan this issue be re-opened as a feature request, or is this considered a `wontfix`?\r\n\r\nMy use-case is that this allows \"docked\" windows that has a different `Normal` color to blend better with its border. The current behavior works well for file explorer plugins that docks to the left by default, but not so much for plugins that docks to the bottom or any other direction.",
