        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> If 'winhighlight' is set on a window, its WinSeparator highlights all borders.\r\n\r\nYes.\r\n\r\n> If 'winhighlight' is set on multiple adjacent windows how is the priority decided?\r\n\r\nYeah, I think this should be discussed. Not sure what's the simplest way of resolving the conflict. I was thinking that it should be based on when `setlocal` was called (the newest `setlocal` takes priority). But does that mean that you need to store additional timestamp metadata? Or is there a simpler heuristic?\r\n\r\nWhat do you think?",
